name: Al Jazeera PR
content: Enroll now in the English version of the #AlJazeera_Fellowship 2021 (Special Edition). The Al Jazeera Fellowship gives participants the chance to produce academic research on the latest developments in journalism and the challenges facing the field as a whole, under the supervision of experts and academics who are a part of the Al Jazeera Media Network. The program will last for three months, and participants will have the opportunity to learn first-hand as a part of the Al Jazeera team. They will also attend training sessions with editors-in-chiefs, journalists, and researchers in the Al Jazeera Media Network, which will help the participants with their research project. To see how to apply for the Al Jazeera Fellowship, please click on the following link and fill out the application formhttps://institute.aljazeera.net/en/fellowship.

Mr. Khan's claims that Al Jazeera is reporting false stories and trying ما‎ instigate violence in Kashmir are both unfounded and alarming. We categorically reject his allegations and stand by the quality and accuracy of our journalism. As an international news organization, Al Jazeera adheres to the highest standards of professionalism and objectivity. We always seek all sides of any story to ensure balance in our coverage.
